& [SearchQuestion] is the bounded inquiry
  + [question] is whether accepted local pressure-decomposition or pressure-regularity literature contains a lemma close to tail_budget_controls_same_cylinder_pressure_L3_over_2_or_pressure_oscillation_smallness
  + [target_quantity] is same-cylinder scale-invariant pressure L3_over_2 or pressure oscillation smallness
  + [target_context] is CKN-style local epsilon regularity for suitable weak solutions

& [CandidateConversionNeighborhood] is the source scan
  + [candidate_001_local_pressure_decomposition] is local suitable weak solution pressure decomposition with harmonic component
    = source: Wolf-local-suitable-solution literature as represented by local boundedness and local pressure decomposition expositions
    = source_url: https://sebastian-hensel.com/master_thesis.pdf
    = fit: high_background
    = reading: this gives the correct decomposition vocabulary, but not the project-specific tail-budget smallness conversion
    = blocker: decomposition is structural; smallness still must be proved in the same cylinder
  + [candidate_002_local_pressure_estimates] is local pressure estimates inside epsilon-regularity frameworks
    = source: Guevara and Phuc, Local energy bounds and epsilon-regularity criteria for the 3D Navier-Stokes equations
    = source_url: https://www.math.lsu.edu/~pcnguyen/papers_html/Guevara-Phuc-12-29-16.pdf
    = fit: strongest_audit_support
    = reading: useful for line-auditing how pressure quantities are estimated from local energy and larger-scale terms
    = blocker: still does not identify the project tail budget as one of the accepted pressure quantities
  + [candidate_003_pressure_role_partial_regularity] is pressure-centered partial regularity and dissipative/local suitable frameworks
    = source: Chamorro, Lemarie-Rieusset, and Mayoufi pressure-role line, plus later ETH pressure-role work
    = source_url: https://www.research-collection.ethz.ch/bitstreams/1c1170b9-dc9d-4f74-a4d5-b8479bb403bf/download
    = fit: medium_high_context
    = reading: clarifies that pressure treatment is central and subtle in partial regularity
    = blocker: not yet a narrow same-cylinder tail-to-pressure-smallness lemma
  + [candidate_004_harmonic_pressure_caution] is finite-scale harmonic-pressure caution
    = source: arXiv 2606.08352 Finite-Scale One-Component Regularity via Harmonic Pressure
    = source_url: https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.08352
    = fit: cautionary
    = reading: harmonic pressure can have bounded scale-invariant L3_over_2 oscillation while pointwise gradient behavior is bad under time concentration
    = blocker: strengthens the need to track harmonic/nonlocal pressure separately rather than bundling it into a tail budget
  + [candidate_005_pressure_conditions_local_regular_regularization] is older pressure conditions for local regularity
    = source: Neustupa and Penel, Pressure conditions for local regularity of solutions of the Navier-Stokes equations
    = source_url: https://emis.de/ft/511
    = fit: pressure_criterion_candidate
    = reading: gives pressure-specific local regularity conditions that may help select a theorem statement
    = blocker: must be checked against exact exponents, weak-solution class, and locality before use

